               <note>
                  <ab type="description">ʾAbun Bet is a quarter north-west of the castles in
                        <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>. It was the residence of
                     the Metropolitan (<roleName type="title">ʾabun</roleName>) and a place of
                     asylum. Its location changed over the centuries: it was first located near
                        <placeName ref="LOC6540Entone">ʾAbbā ʾƎnṭonǝs</placeName> church; then, in
                     the second half of the <date>18th century</date>, it was moved near <placeName ref="LOC6539Gabrǝel">Gābrǝʾel</placeName> church; finally, during the
                     Italian occupation, it was briefly moved near <placeName ref="LOC6541DabraSahaySell">Dabra Ḍaḥay Śǝllāse</placeName> before the site
                     near <placeName ref="LOC6539Gabrǝel">Gābrǝʾel</placeName> church was restored
                     following the Italians' expulsion in <date>1941</date>.</ab>
               </note>
